<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="description" content="Carrier Bag Levy" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Compostable Carrier Liners – Request for bag levy exemption</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Global Trading UK Limited.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">1. Introduction</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.1  Global Trading UK Limited is a family-run packaging company based in Preston in the North West of England. The company has been providing innovative packaging solutions to UK supermarkets and high-street retailers for over 35 years. We are currently a leading supplier of recyclable, reusable, bio-renewable and compostable packaging.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">2. Summary</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.1  One of the products that we are concerned will be affected by the forthcoming bag levy is the Compostable Carrier-Liner. This is a strong, lightweight shopping bag which is specially designed to be reused as a food waste kitchen caddy-liner. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.2  Global helped to develop this product at the request of The Co-operative and the bags are currently  on sale at most Co-op stores in England and Scotland where food waste collections take place. The Co-op sells the bag at cost (for 6p). Sales to date have been in the region of 5.9 million bags per annum, although in 2014 the number of stockist was increased to 600 stores. The projected sales figure is now 15 million bags per annum.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.3  By offering customers the option to buy this dual-purpose bag at the till, several million fewer plastic carrier bags are distributed annually by The Co-op.  The bag has features which make it highly popular as a caddy-liner and its availability has been proven to increase participation and retention rates in council food waste collection programmes.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.4  To build on the popularity of The Co-op bag, Global recently set up the Green Carrier Scheme (GCS). This is a new initiative to make carrier-liners more widely available at smaller shops and convenience stores throughout the UK. Under the scheme, councils will subsidise the 6p cost price of the bags to make them available to buy for just 3 or 4 pence. This is a third of the price of caddy-liners sold on a roll. Local retailers recruited into the scheme can make a small profit on the sale of each bag and can also save money by not buying as many conventional plastic bags.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.5  We believe that the GCS will:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Help councils save money and minimise food waste contamination issues. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Help ensure profitability for Britain’s food waste industry. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Reduce the number of plastic carrier bags in circulation. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Benefit retailers by encouraging new and repeat business for scheme members.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.6  The GCS project has the support of several compostable film manufacturers including </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Novamont</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (Mater-Bi) BASF (Eco-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Vio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">) and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Biotec</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Bioplast</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> 500). The bags are currently made in Italy but could easily be made in the UK and this option is currently being investigated.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.7  Global (and The Co-operative) are concerned that the current bag levy regulations do not classify carrier-liners as reusable bags, because the secondary use (caddy-liner) is not a repetition of the original use (shopping). This interpretation of the word reusable means that carrier-liners could be treated as single-use carriers and subject to the charge.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">3. Proposal</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.1  We are requesting that carrier-liners are classified as reusable bags and granted exemption from the forthcoming single-use bag levy. Our proposal is based on the grounds that they:</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Are a paid-for item and not distributed free of charge.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Have a dedicated secondary use (rather than an optional secondary use).</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Have a predictable method of disposal, so are unlikely to wind up in landfill.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Are highly unlikely to ever become an item of litter.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Have been proven to reduce the contamination of food waste collections.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Have been proven to improve participation and retention rates in food waste programmes.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.2  We would recommend the following provisos:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.3  The bag must be of a suitable size for reuse in kitchen caddies. For example, a compostable bag designed to carry a suit jacket would be impractical to use as a caddy-liner and would more likely wind up in landfill. We would recommend that the dimensions of The Co-operative compostable carrier are used to set this criterion.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.4  The bag should carry instructions for consumers as to its intended purpose, along with a warning not to recycle the bag with other plastic films. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.5  The bag material should be EN13432 certified. If the ‘Seedling’ logo is used a ‘P’ number manufacturer tracking code should be displayed. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.6  In </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Global’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> experience, some industrial composting companies require compostable films to biodegrade faster than the EN13432 pass limit of 180 days. Ideally, bags entering the market as carrier-liners would need to be made of a material which is approved by representatives of the UK composting industry. </span></li></ul><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">5. Declaration of Interest</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">5.1   Global Trading UK Limited declares an interest as the current supplier of this product to The Co-operative. If the GCS concept proves to be successful, it is likely that councils would be required to tender for carrier-liner supplies. Global therefore plan to operate the GCS as a separate not-for-profit business and charge for consultancy, supply tender management (for quality control) order processing facilities, marketing and food-waste education.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">6. </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.1   The food waste collected by Britain’s councils is sold to industrial composting companies who use it to create compost and bio-gas. Unfortunately, if the waste is contaminated with even small fragments of plastic it becomes worthless. Contaminated batches are generally sent to landfill which incurs a biodegradable-waste charge (at the council's expense) and the council can also face a fine from the composting company. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.2   The tolerance level for plastic in food waste has recently been reduced to 0.5 percent, so contamination is becoming a serious problem for an increasing number of local authorities. </span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">7. The </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">Current Position</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.1   Councils have a number of options to help minimise contamination issues: </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Issue a ‘starter pack’ of compostable kitchen caddy-liners, then ask residents to buy them. This encourages initial participation, but retention rates can suffer in the long term.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Distribute compostable liners free of charge. Doing this also encourages initial participation, but there are drawbacks in the medium to long term: </span><br /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.2   It is expensive </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Liner purchasing costs hundreds of thousands of pounds annually. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Council-tax payers carry the burden, so liners are certainly not ‘free’. </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.3   It is wasteful </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Not every liner recipient participates in food waste collection. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Unwanted compostable liners wind up in general waste. </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.4   It is inefficient </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Small, handle-less caddy-liners cannot be filled properly. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Councils are not maximising their potential food waste volumes. </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.5   It can discourage participation</span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Cheap liner material splits easily resulting in spillage. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">If handling food waste is unpleasant, residents will stop doing it.</span><br /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ul></ul><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">8. </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">The Compostable Carrier</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold"> Liner</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.1   In 2006, The Co-operative commissioned packaging supplier Global Trading UK Limited to create a compostable carrier bag which could be reused as a food waste caddy liner. Global worked with bio-plastic manufacturer </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Novamont</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">S.p.A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and developed the dual-purpose product. The bag was designed to be slightly smaller than a conventional supermarket carrier to ensure that it fitted caddies properly. The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Novamont</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> material used for the bag is a market leading compostable film, so it meets with the approval of most UK industrial composting processors.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.2   The product benefits:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A strong shopping bag.</span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Successfully jog tested at 8 kg/3mins – 2kg over the specification of 6 Kg/3mins.</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A no-mess caddy-liner. </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Long handles mean no contact with rotting food. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Easy to tie the bag.</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Stronger than most ‘free’ caddy-liners. </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Less chance of splitting. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Keeps kerbside collection bins cleaner.</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Larger capacity than most ‘free’ caddy-liners. </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Caddies can be fully filled (under-filling is a common problem).</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Made from EN Certified compostable film. </span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Compostable film is made by market-leading manufacturers. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Film is already widely accepted by UK industrial composters. </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Suitable for home and municipal composting.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">An environmentally-friendly product.</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A paid-for item with a dedicated primary and secondary use. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Predictable method of disposal. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Unlikely to become an item of litter. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Lightweight and compact to transport. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Second use reduces overall carbon impact.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.3   The Co-op sell the bags responsibly and they are only on sale in stores where food waste collection takes place and where it is known that the council will accept certified compostable liners. </span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">9. An award winning solution</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">9.1   In 2007 Oldham Council entered into an informal price and availability agreement with the Co-operative and asked residents to buy the compostable carriers to use as caddy-liners. This resulted in a higher than expected participation and retention rate for their food waste programme. The partnership between the council and a retailer was the first of its kind and in 2010 the project won two environmental packaging awards. </span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">10. </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">The Green Carrier Scheme</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold"> (GCS)</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">10.1   Although the availability of the Co-operative Compostable Carrier is increasing each year, it has become clear that the project would benefit from being extended to other retailers. Oldham Council was keen to pilot this idea, so in November 2013 Global launched The Green Carrier Scheme (GCS). The scheme is designed to appeal to councils with high plastic contamination rates, high disposal costs and low food waste revenue. The council would mitigate this by subsidising the cost of compostable carrier-liners to make them extremely affordable for residents and then incentivise local retailers to sell them.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">10.2   The benefits for councils are:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The subsidy can be less than the cost of disposal of contaminated waste.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The subsidy can be less than the revenue lost through contamination issues.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The scheme presents an opportunity to engage with local businesses and residents. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Councils can prioritise recruitment of stockists in areas where contamination is highest. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">10.3   Participating retailers can:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Save money by buying less plastic carrier bags.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Sell a low cost product which has proven to be popular with customers.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Become an ‘official’ stockist of a council approved product (bags carry the council logo).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Make a small profit on the sale of each bag (between £5.00 and £10.00 per case of 1,000).</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">10.4   The role of the GCS is to:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Set and manage the bag specification based on known performance criteria.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Source the bags, or manage any tender process to ensure quality standards are met.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Provide facilities that will enable retailers to order online and by telephone.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Allow cash-on-delivery payment to allow very small businesses to participate.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Provide councils and retailers with marketing support.</span></li></ul><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">11. </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">The Oldham Council </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">GCS </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">Trial</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">11.1   In November 2013, Oldham Council started a trial of the Green Carrier Scheme. Food waste rejected due to plastic contamination costs the council £211.00 per tonne. The estimated total cost of rejected loads and loss of food waste revenue is £400,000 each year.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">11.2   </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Trial Method</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The council subsidised the carrier-liner retail price to 3p (cost price is 6p).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The bags were sold to retailers for 2p enabling a 1p profit per bag sold.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">25 small shops were recruited as stockist in the target area.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The test encompassed 10,000 households in an area where contamination was high.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 1) A door-to-door campaign to educate residents about the problems.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 2) Green-tagging of any collection bins that were contaminated (a final warning).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 3) Red-tagging of contaminated bins (and a refusal to collect).</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">11.3   </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Trial Results (Westwood area)</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 1) 394 Green-tagged bins.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 2) 266 Red tagged bins.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Week 3) 27 Red tagged bins.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Total collected = 11.52 tonnes of high quality food waste.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Bags sold = 14,400 at a cost to the council of £432.00</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Savings of having no rejected loads  = £2,431.00</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Total saving in first three weeks of the trial = </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">circa </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">£2,000</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">11.4   Participant </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Feedback</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Resident engagement = Over 90% positive. Local availability is seen as the key benefit.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Product performance feedback = Cheapest and best quality caddy-liner on the market.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Contamination level after first 3 weeks of the trial = </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">0</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> %</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Waste disposal authority feedback = very happy. No quality issues at all.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Shopkeeper feedback = A noticeable increase in footfall (+10% average). </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A copy of the full report</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> from Oldham Council is available on request.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">12. Conclusion</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">12.1   Although a compostable carrier-liner has the same shape as a plastic carrier bag, it has a dedicated secondary purpose which offers many environmental and commercial benefits. We hope that the process to grant exemptions for the levy will take these factors into account and allow the product to be sold without any additional charge.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">13. Further</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold"> information:</span><br /><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a href="http://www.greencarrierscheme.org"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">www.greencarrierscheme.org</span></a></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a href="http://www.responsiblepackaging.co.uk"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">www.responsiblepackaging.co.uk</span></a></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a href="http://www.gtuk.co.uk"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">www.gtuk.co.uk</span></a></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">23 January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>